info.headline: Flood Watch issued December 10 at 4:14AM PST until December 11 at 1:32AM PST by NWS Seattle
info.description: .A flood warning has been issued for the Skokomish River in Mason County. ...FLOOD WATCH IN EFFECT FROM 1 PM PST THIS AFTERNOON THROUGH LATE MONDAY NIGHT... * WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall is possible. * WHERE...Portions of northwest and west central Washington, including the following counties, in northwest Washington, Grays Harbor. In west central Washington, Lewis and Thurston. * WHEN...From 1 PM PST this afternoon through late Monday night. * IMPACTS...Excessive runoff may result in flooding of rivers, creeks, streams, and other low-lying and flood-prone locations. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - Heavy rain in higher elevations of central and southern western Washington could cause river flooding beginning this afternoon. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
info.instruction: You should monitor later forecasts and be alert for possible Flood Warnings. Those living in areas prone to flooding should be prepared to take action should flooding develop.
